  <h1>
   current_weekday
  </h1>
  This
  <b>
   read only
  </b>
  variable will return the weekday as a value, where Sunday is 0 and Saturday is 6.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">current_weekday;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">var day;
switch(current_weekday)
{
    case 0: day = "Sunday"; break;
    case 1: day = "Monday"; break;
    case 2: day = "Tuesday"; break;
    case 3: day = "Wednesday"; break;
    case 4: day = "Thursday"; break;
    case 5: day = "Friday"; break;
    case 6: day = "Saturday"; break;
}
draw_text(32, 32, "Today is " + day +".");
</code></pre>
  The above code uses the
  <span>
   current_weekday
  </span>
  value to set a variable with the correct day in text, then draws that for the user to see.
 </body>
</html>